According to the prosecutor’s office, the tender funds won were used for their own purposes, and the performance of the tasks was often verified with untrue invoices.
State and municipal funds – in total HUF 65 million – migrated partly to the cash register of the Young Left and partly into the pockets of certain persons.
The method presented by the investigating authority was that the tender funds won were taken up on the basis of cost invoices, behind which there was no real performance, and the associations never fulfilled the agreed obligation.
According to the indictment, most of the accounts were false.
For these, the invoice blocks were purchased in the market of Józsefváros, and the round stamps were produced in Kiskunhalas.
And to which companies the account production should take place, among others, it was decided on the Balaton-felvidéki boulevard to which János Zuschlag sent István Lados.
According to the testimony of the latter, it had to look like pensions and restaurants.
He asked for an invoice for his consumption there, and modelled on which invoices were drawn up for applications to be submitted to the applications of the Ministry of Youth and Sport, the Ministry of Social Affairs and Labour, and the Municipality of Budapest.
Most of them were written by István Lados with his partner, András Őri, who, according to our information, mostly wrote the reports necessary to win the subsidies.
